13:25.847 --> 13:28.515
[LAUGHING]

13:28.515 --> 13:29.183
See?

13:29.183 --> 13:31.602
You're not enjoying this.

13:31.602 --> 13:32.061
Oh, shut up.

13:32.061 --> 13:34.771
It wouldn't have bothered
me at all.

13:34.771 --> 13:35.606
Oh, come on.

13:35.606 --> 13:38.025
Jeff, we have
been married 14 years,

13:38.025 --> 13:38.985
we both have pasts.

13:38.985 --> 13:40.236
It's just not a big deal.

13:40.236 --> 13:43.614
Well, I know, it's just that...

13:43.614 --> 13:45.282
Well, you know...

13:45.282 --> 13:46.158
What?

13:46.158 --> 13:49.078
None of yours are famous.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.580
[LAUGHING]

13:51.580 --> 13:52.206
Famous?

13:52.206 --> 13:55.084
Oh, please,
she's a dancing chimp

13:55.084 --> 13:56.752
whose 15 minutes
are just about up.

13:56.752 --> 13:59.255
Oh, I knew you'd turn on her.
[AUDREY SCOFFS]

13:59.255 --> 14:01.757
Besides, it's not like
I haven't dated

14:01.757 --> 14:02.925
someone well-known.

14:02.925 --> 14:03.592
Not this again, Audrey,

14:03.592 --> 14:06.553
I wouldn't call the guy who grew
the largest pumpkin

14:06.553 --> 14:10.349
in Lancaster County
"well-known."

14:10.349 --> 14:13.560
It wasn't just Lancaster, it was
the whole tri-county area,

14:13.560 --> 14:15.812
and that's not
who I'm talking about.

14:15.812 --> 14:17.148
I dated somebody more famous.

14:17.148 --> 14:19.483
Really? More famous
than Punkin' Pete?

14:19.483 --> 14:21.818
It just so happens
my first year of college

14:21.818 --> 14:24.738
I had quite the little fling
with Jerry Waldman.

14:24.738 --> 14:26.657
Who's Jerry Waldman?

14:26.657 --> 14:27.950
Oh, just a brilliant
law student

14:27.950 --> 14:30.661
who would eventually go on
to become... Here we go...

14:30.661 --> 14:35.707
The Chief Justice of the Supreme
Court of the State of New York.

14:35.707 --> 14:37.919
Really? You, uh-- You dated him?
Yep.

14:37.919 --> 14:41.088
The Honorable Jerome Waldman.

14:41.088 --> 14:43.215
Ha, he's bald.

14:43.215 --> 14:45.717
Mine's hot and yours
is a chrome dome.

14:45.717 --> 14:49.263
He is the youngest Supreme Court
Justice in history.

14:49.263 --> 14:51.765
A genius at constitutional law.

14:51.765 --> 14:52.516
Because he was studying

14:52.516 --> 14:54.685
while everyone else
was combing their hair.

14:54.685 --> 14:56.938
He had a thick head
of hair when I dated him.

14:56.938 --> 14:58.647
It's too bad things
didn't work out

14:58.647 --> 15:01.858
because you could've been
Mrs. Audrey Baldman.

15:01.858 --> 15:03.485
It's Waldman.

15:03.485 --> 15:05.404
Not anymore.

15:06.447 --> 15:08.324
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

15:08.324 --> 15:09.075
RUSSELL:
Hey, Timmy.

15:09.075 --> 15:11.493
Hello, sir.
I was worried sick about you.

15:11.493 --> 15:12.494
So did you do it?
I did.

15:12.494 --> 15:15.247
And it actually went quite well.
It turns out she felt

15:15.247 --> 15:17.458
much the same way I did
and was also relieved.

15:17.458 --> 15:21.253
Great. Okay, to recap
and be totally clear:

15:21.253 --> 15:22.796
You're totally broken up,

15:22.796 --> 15:23.880
all ties cut, no regrets,

15:23.880 --> 15:26.300
and you have no feelings
for her whatsoever.

15:26.300 --> 15:29.595
Well, I don't know if--
Yes or no?

15:31.180 --> 15:32.014
Yes.

15:32.014 --> 15:33.975
Suneetha and I are un-engaged.
Hm.

15:33.975 --> 15:36.227
And we were even able
to remain friends.

15:36.227 --> 15:37.228
And I have you to thank, sir.

15:37.228 --> 15:39.855
I wish there was
some way I could repay you.

15:39.855 --> 15:43.985
Well, there might be.

15:43.985 --> 15:45.236
Oh, really? How?

15:45.236 --> 15:49.615
Oh, I don't know,
maybe give me her number?

15:49.615 --> 15:51.242
Her phone number?

15:51.242 --> 15:52.784
Hm.

15:52.784 --> 15:53.869
Why?

15:53.869 --> 15:56.247
[TIMMY LAUGHING]

16:06.382 --> 16:08.134
You told him, huh?

16:08.134 --> 16:09.635
What's so funny?

16:09.635 --> 16:10.469
What I feel for Suneetha--

16:10.469 --> 16:13.680
Oh, you feel, do you, sir?
That's a good one!

16:13.680 --> 16:16.558
Do you seriously believe
she would go from a young,

16:16.558 --> 16:19.770
taut-skinned, reasonably
attractive man of her same caste

16:19.770 --> 16:21.938
with a great head
of jet-black hair to--

16:21.938 --> 16:24.316
Well,
the opposite of all that?

16:25.359 --> 16:27.403
Wow. That is really mean.

16:27.403 --> 16:30.197
Spend a day at my house,
I'll show you mean.

16:30.197 --> 16:33.909
I don't care what you say.
I've never felt this way before.

16:33.909 --> 16:35.244
I do hope
she can hear your voice

16:35.244 --> 16:40.332
from the splat of her vomit
hitting the sidewalk.

16:40.332 --> 16:41.583
So mean.

16:41.583 --> 16:43.669
Now, if your mind
is really made up,

16:43.669 --> 16:46.547
I suggest you get a move on.
She's going back to India.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.840
She'll be leaving
from the airport soon.

16:48.840 --> 16:51.760
What?
Why didn't you tell me?

16:51.760 --> 16:54.596
Come on. How do I look?

16:54.596 --> 16:57.224
Like Martina Navratilova.

16:57.224 --> 16:57.933
Yeah?

16:57.933 --> 17:01.395
She's a handsome woman.
I'll take it.

17:02.271 --> 17:03.480
See ya.

17:03.480 --> 17:08.319
Well, this is a new low,
even for him.

17:08.319 --> 17:08.735
What is?

17:08.735 --> 17:11.197
To pretend he had
my interests at heart.

17:11.197 --> 17:13.532
But it was all just
a facade to get rid of me

17:13.532 --> 17:16.702
so he could make
a move on Suneetha.

17:16.702 --> 17:17.994
Uh, listen, Timmy,

17:17.994 --> 17:19.663
Russell's not always
a great guy.

17:19.663 --> 17:21.082
[SIGHS]
But I gotta defend him here.

17:21.082 --> 17:25.086
He's been in love with Suneetha
since he first laid eyes on her.

17:25.086 --> 17:26.962
I'm sorry, what?

17:26.962 --> 17:27.463
It's true.

17:27.463 --> 17:30.341
But he didn't do anything
out of respect for you.

17:30.341 --> 17:31.758
He waited
till you broke up

17:31.758 --> 17:35.096
and made sure
it was your decision.

17:37.223 --> 17:40.184
I can't quite believe it. Um--

17:40.184 --> 17:42.018
Oh, perhaps I was wrong
about him.

17:42.018 --> 17:46.107
Mm-hm. Well, maybe you should've
paid a little more attention.

17:46.107 --> 17:49.235
Glad I'm not your best friend.

17:49.818 --> 17:52.779
I mean, unless you want
me to be.

17:52.779 --> 17:55.866
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

17:57.618 --> 17:58.285
Suneetha, wait.

17:58.285 --> 18:01.455
You got time, buddy,
this is gonna take a while.

18:01.455 --> 18:03.624
Russell,
what are you doing here?

18:03.624 --> 18:07.961
I-- I just--
I wanted to tell you that...

18:08.129 --> 18:10.214
God, this is harder
than I thought.

18:10.214 --> 18:12.591
That's what she said.

18:12.591 --> 18:15.427
I got that from you.
It makes me laugh every time.

18:15.427 --> 18:18.722
Yeah, well, that's solid, it's
one of the classics.

18:18.722 --> 18:20.015
We have so much in common.

18:20.015 --> 18:21.892
We like the same jokes.

18:21.892 --> 18:25.521
Uh, you're smart and beautiful,
and I'm smart and...

18:25.521 --> 18:28.149
Do you know who
Martina Navratilova is?

18:28.149 --> 18:31.318
Yes. She's a handsome woman.

18:31.318 --> 18:31.902
Thank you.

18:31.902 --> 18:33.237
Listen,
I know this is crazy,

18:33.237 --> 18:35.614
and it's sudden,
but I actually--

18:35.614 --> 18:38.117
Me too, Russell.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.075
What?

18:39.075 --> 18:41.453
Since that first day
at the airport,

18:41.453 --> 18:44.080
I've had these
feelings for you as well.

18:44.080 --> 18:45.957
You have? Really?

18:45.957 --> 18:49.545
I tried to hide them,
I didn't want Timmy to know.

18:49.545 --> 18:51.547
Well, Timmy knows.
I just told him.

18:51.547 --> 18:54.216
It's on the up and up now,
there's nothing to hide.

18:54.216 --> 18:58.179
You can take that trunk out.
You gotta be kidding me.

18:58.179 --> 19:00.055
Russell, as much as
I'd love to stay

19:00.055 --> 19:02.015
and see where this goes,
I can't.

19:02.015 --> 19:04.226
I must return to Mumbai.

19:04.226 --> 19:04.810
No.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.645
But we'll always
have this moment.

19:06.645 --> 19:12.276
This perfect moment
will just belong to us.

19:16.280 --> 19:18.782
Goodbye, Russell.

19:22.411 --> 19:24.371
Goodbye, sweet Suneetha.

19:26.039 --> 19:28.500
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

19:31.253 --> 19:33.797
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

19:35.757 --> 19:37.759
Hello?

19:37.759 --> 19:39.094
Oh, hi.

19:39.094 --> 19:42.306
Yes, how'd it go?

19:42.306 --> 19:43.807
Really?

19:43.807 --> 19:44.475
And then what?

19:44.475 --> 19:48.061
Then I kissed him goodbye
and got in the cab.

19:48.061 --> 19:51.147
Thank you so much for doing
that for me, Suneetha.

19:51.147 --> 19:54.109
That was very sweet
and most generous of you.

19:54.109 --> 19:55.527
I was happy to do it.

19:55.527 --> 20:00.532
You know, uh, I wonder if we may
have acted a bit hastily

20:00.532 --> 20:04.703
in calling off our engagement.

20:04.703 --> 20:05.662
Suneetha?

20:05.662 --> 20:10.959
Oh, I'm sorry, I was just
thinking about Russell.

20:10.959 --> 20:12.878
He is very sweet

20:12.878 --> 20:15.297
andkind of sexy in a--

20:15.297 --> 20:18.133
Safe travels, goodbye.

20:18.133 --> 20:20.302
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:22.263 --> 20:23.639
MAN [ON TV]:
And in news from Albany,

20:23.639 --> 20:27.268
today New York State Supreme
Court Justice Jerry Waldman

20:27.268 --> 20:28.810
made a dramatic announcement:

20:28.810 --> 20:31.355
WALDMAN:
In the interests
of living my life

20:31.355 --> 20:35.108
from here forward in an honest
and truthful way,

20:35.108 --> 20:38.862
I would like to say
on the record

20:38.862 --> 20:41.823
that I am gay.

20:42.949 --> 20:45.827
I am a gay American.

20:45.827 --> 20:46.953
JEFF:
Oh, my God!

20:46.953 --> 20:49.498
Audrey! Get in here!

20:49.498 --> 20:51.708
Baldman's gay!

20:51.708 --> 20:54.169
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]

20:55.796 --> 20:58.299
[♪♪♪♪♪♪]
